cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL

The paper discusses security issues related to CUDA, which is a platform for GPU computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also suggests software patches and alternative approaches, which indicates that it may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves architecture-related vulnerabilities, which could fall under cs.AR (Architecture). The paper also experiments with the AES encryption algorithm, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
